Package: SAfeR
Type: Package
Title: Visualization tools for SA Crime Stats
Version: 0.1
Date: 2017-07-03
Author: c(person("Aida", "Ylanan", email = "a1daylanan@ucla.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
          person("Jason", "Chong", "jasonchongg@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
          person("Paola", "Scaramuzzi", "pascar18@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: This package offers a deep insight on South African crime rates between 2005 and 2015. It allows users to obtain information for specific years, geographic areas (provinces and stations) and types of crime. On top of this, it allows the user to create useful visualizations of the data.
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Imports: dplyr, ggplot2, ggthemes, forcats, tidyr, reshape2
Suggests: testthat
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
